<div><h3>SOC 141 - The Sociology of Mental Illness </h3>  <hr>This course will examine the experience of mental illness and the disparities in diagnosis according to race, gender, and class.  It will also consider mental health institutions and the cycles of institutional reform.  In addition, the course will explore the recent &#8220;happiness movement&#8221; and what it means to be mentally healthy in American society today.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> bi-annually<br><br></div>		</td>
